Step 1: Identify the relevant end-of-period amounts. From the balance sheet:
 • Total Assets at the end = 12,385,382.42  
 • Total Current Liabilities (the only liabilities provided) = 737,762.05

Step 2: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio using the formula:  
 Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets

Step 3: Plug in the values:
 Debt to Asset Ratio = 737,762.05 / 12,385,382.42 ≈ 0.0596

Step 4: Rounding the result to two decimal places gives approximately 0.06.

Thus, the final solution in the required format is:

{
  "solution": {"Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.06"}
}
